b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":1176,"category_name":"Events","pr_category_id":"4","title_name":"The Event Compendium, Which Lets You Replay Past Events Any Time, Has Been Added! [Updated]","message":"<div>The Event Compendium was added to recurring events at <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1585288800\\"><\/span>!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1643090400\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><br>The list of available events included in this notification will no longer be updated. Information on events added to the Event Compendium in the future will appear in a separate notification.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/4d660958cb5bbba98b4b0971b64e5367.png\\"><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Compendium Overview<\/div><div>In the Event Compendium, you can play some past events any time you like. To participate, select the banner in Event Compendium from the Recurring Events section under Quests.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Compendium Unlock Conditions<\/div><div>The Event Compendium will unlock when you clear chapter 2 \/ 2-1, The Sylvan Archer (Normal).<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Participating in Event Compendium Quests<\/div><div>To play Event Compendium quests, you must participate in an event. You can change which event you are participating in at any time, but you may only participate in one event at a time.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIf you switch which event you are participating in, the quests you have cleared and endeavors you have completed will carry over to the next time you participate in the event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Data Downloads<\/div><div>A data download will occur whenever you participate in an event in the Event Compendium. If you switch which event you are participating in, the data for the event you were participating in will be deleted and data will be downloaded for the new event you have selected.<\/div><div>\\u30fbEven if event data is deleted, the quests you have cleared and endeavors you have completed will carry over to the next time you participate in the event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Quests<\/div><div>Some quests available using the Event Compendium differ from the quests when the event was held as a limited-time event in the past. Some drop rewards will also differ.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Treasure Trade<\/div><div>You can trade event items obtained in the Event Compendium for various rewards. There will be some differences between the Treasure Trade lineup and the lineup from when the event was held as a limited-time event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Endeavors<\/div><div>The event endeavors for the event you are participating in using the Event Compendium will display in the Normal tab under Endeavors. There are no daily and limited endeavors. Also, some endeavors will differ from when the event was held as a limited-time event in the past.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Items<\/div><div>The number of facility level-up materials held when the facility events were held as limited-time events in the past will carry over to the same facility event within the Event Compendium.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Facilities<\/div><div>Facilities obtained during facility events within the Event Compendium increase the stats of adventurers. They also confer a special effect that lets you deal more damage to enemies in quests for the facility event where the facility was obtained. The strength of this effect increases as you level up the event facility.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>To level up facilities, you&#39;ll need materials that can be obtained in facility event quests. The materials required to level up event facilities differ based on the event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Bonuses<\/div><div>For each facility event in the Event Compendium, there are wyrmprints that have bonus effects during that event. These wyrmprints can be obtained as endeavor rewards, or from the Treasure Trade for wyrmprints. Switching between events will also switch which wyrmprints appear on the Featured tab in the Treasure Trade for wyrmprints.<br>\\u30fbThe amount of event bonus effect differs based on the wyrmprint and how much the wyrmprint has been unbound.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><br>\\u25a0Available Events <span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\">[Updated at <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1621231200\\"><\/span>]<\/span><br>The following twelve events are available starting at <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1621231200\\"><\/span>.<br><br>If chapter 2 \/ 2-1 of the main campaign is cleared on Normal difficulty:<br>\\u30fbFlames of Reflection (facility event)<br>\\u30fbThe Miracle of Dragonyule (facility event)<br>\\u30fbA Wish to the Winds (facility event)<br>\\u30fbDream Big Under the Big Top (facility event)<br>\\u30fbThe Hunt for Harmony (facility event)<br>\\u30fbTrick or Treasure! (facility event)<br>\\u30fbA Crescendo of Courage (facility event)<br>\\u30fbThe Accursed Archives (facility event)<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Fire Emblem: Lost Heroes Event<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Fire Emblem: Kindred Ties Event<br><br>If chapter 6 \/ 4-4 of the main campaign is cleared on Normal difficulty:<br>\\u30fbFractured Futures (raid event)<br><br>If chapter 14 \/ 4-9 &nbsp;of the main campaign is cleared on Normal difficulty:<br>\\u30fbForgotten Truths (raid event)<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Notes:<\/div><div>\\u30fbAll quests added this time are solo-only quests and cannot be played in co-op.<\/div><div>\\u30fbMore events will be made available in future updates.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1585288800,"prev_article_id":"1140","next_article_id":"1161","image_path":"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/4d660958cb5bbba98b4b0971b64e5367.png","update_time":1643092231}}}'